As the title says, Epilogue annotation logging works just fine when deployed to the physical robot, but when I run the code in simulation, none of the logged values show up in NetworkTables. I have tried fiddling with the Epilogue configs, calling Epilogue.update manually in different periodic methods, changing what classes are tagged as @Logged, but nothing seems to fix it. At one point, Epilogue was logging its stats (runtime), but that has since disappeared seemingly without reason. I also have tried with my Windows firewall off, which does not seem to affect the issue.

Any ideas? Thanks in advance!

Here’s the link to our repository:
https://github.com/hammerheads5000/2025Reefscape

Okay, I finally got this fixed.

In my WPILib VSCode settings I had to set Java > Server: Launch Mode to Hybrid and enable Java > Debug > Settings: Force Build Before Launch. I then was able to restart WPILib, delete and redownload the repository, and then it worked.

I’m assuming there was something wrong with how the Java server was generating logging files because now bin/generated-sources/annotations is empty unlike its counterpart in /build/, although I’m not exactly sure how this would affect things.
